"This beer really benefits with a little breathing. The cherry opens up wide and the experience overall is more enjoyable. This is a good take on a cherry forward Berliner from the fine people at Schell's. It doesn't quite match the lofty expectations of the original but it's still excellent and sitting even shouldered with the other two releases. Worth drinking without a doubt."
