"Light bodied. Lively carbonation. Easy drinking."
"This is far better than most American fruit wheat beers.  If you want a very tart cherry brew, and can find this, get it before it is gone!"
""
"Overall: An exciting beer if you're at all into traditional beers and especially Berliners. Schell has gone to great lengths and you can taste it here. I would recommend chilling but then letting it warm up in the bottle for 15-20 minutes- I thought it was just ok (and very thin) when ice cold, but quite delicious as it warmed up. This is a great way to get those friends who love New Glarus Belgian Red to jump over into more authentic ""sours", as the flavor profile here is much more traditional of a ""sour"" ale (although not as extreme as an American Wild Ale). I really wish it was $10-12 a bottle instead of $13-15. But I will most likely buy another to age until next summer."
